Mosaic SDUI is the published Server-Driven-UI contract: the schema a producer
(the Platform, or a Module) emits and a client (the Shell, a native client)
renders, plus the standard component-definition library and the design tokens.
It is licensed permissively, and independently of the Platform, so a Module may
build its UI against it under any license of the Module author's choosing —
mirroring the SDK's role for the content contract.
